  <section>
    <h2>AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture for Autonomous AI Agents</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Author:</strong> Kenneth Tannenbaum<br />
      <strong>Submitted to:</strong> <em>IEEE Computer</em>, Special Issue on AI Governance and Compliance<br />
      <strong>DOI:</strong> <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19223924">10.5281/zenodo.19223924</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      Presents the AEGIS constitutional governance architecture, which enforces
      governance constraints at the agent action boundary. The framework defines
      a hierarchical authority model where constitutional articles, governance
      policies, and runtime rules constrain autonomous agent behavior before
      actions are executed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>ATX-1: AEGIS Threat Matrix for AI Governance Systems</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Author:</strong> Kenneth Tannenbaum<br />
      <strong>Submitted to:</strong> <em>IEEE Data Descriptions</em><br />
      <strong>DOI:</strong> <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19251098">10.5281/zenodo.19251098</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      A machine-readable threat intelligence dataset in STIX 2.1 format
      cataloging adversarial tactics and techniques targeting AI governance
      systems. ATX-1 defines 10 tactics and 29 techniques that model how
      attackers may attempt to subvert, bypass, or degrade governance controls
      over autonomous AI agents.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture &mdash; NIST AI RMF Position Statement</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Author:</strong> Finnoybu IP LLC<br />
      <strong>Submitted to:</strong> NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)<br />
      <strong>Submitted:</strong> March 7, 2026
    </p>
    <p>
      Formal position paper submitted to NIST on constitutional governance as an
      AI Risk Management Framework implementation pattern. Describes how the
      AEGIS architecture maps to NIST AI RMF functions and provides an
      enforceable governance layer for autonomous AI systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
